{
  "schemaVersion": 1,
  "metadata": {
    "title": "Skyline Forest Run",
    "description": "Hybrid endless-style runner prototype in a stylized forest-stone causeway. The player auto-moves forward on a three-lane track, can switch lanes and jump via mobile-friendly tap zones, collects coins, and avoids spike traps. A 2D HUD overlay shows score and health. Due to engine limits, difficulty scaling, swipe gestures, animations, and meta-progression are simplified or omitted; lane changes and jump are discrete actions mapped to clicks/taps, and there is a fixed-length track that leads to a win scene instead of an infinite endless run.",
    "genre": "unknown"
  },
